import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['size'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Node Sizes')
    plt.axvline(data['size'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['size'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Node Sizes')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of node sizes in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Group by parent node and calculate the average size of nodes
    avg_node_sizes = data.groupby('parent')['size'].mean().reset_index()

    # Create a bar chart of average node sizes grouped by parent node
    plt.bar(avg_node_sizes['parent'], avg_node_sizes['size'])
    plt.xlabel('Parent Node')
    plt.ylabel('Average Node Size')
    plt.title('What is the average size of nodes for each parent node?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    child_counts = data['parent'].value_counts()
    plt.hist(child_counts, bins='auto', color='blue', alpha=0.7, rwidth=0.85)
    plt.xlabel('Number of Child Nodes')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the number of child nodes for each parent node?', wrap=True)
    plt.axvline(child_counts.median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Median: {child_counts.median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    text = ' '.join(data['name'])
    wordcloud = WordCloud(background_color='white', width=800, height=800).generate(text)
    
    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of node names in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
